    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Vincennes, Ind.</placeName>
                <date>Augt. 12. '56</date>
            </p>
            <p>Dr Sir. I had one of your <hi rend="underline">Seriale</hi> Bills<lb/> last
                winter-and the other day, without<lb/> much reflection-gave it to a friend. I<lb/>
                do not remember the price, but I enclose<lb/>
                <hi rend="underline">five dollars</hi>. please send me two copies.<lb/> if the price
                is more, please trust me to<lb/> send you the balance, which I will<lb/> do
                immediately or when I send the Subscription for the occident.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Wrap up in strong paper, direct<lb/> plain, &amp; send by Adams
                Express.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Some time since I recd a copy<lb/> of
                        <persName>Phillipeons<add>?</add></persName> Development from
                    <placeName>London</placeName>,<lb/> and read it with great satisfaction. I<lb/>
                should like to know how you count <persName>Dr.<lb/> P.</persName> is he orthodox or
                not? Count him as<lb/> you may. I feel much that that work<lb/> can only tend to
                elevate the reputation of<lb/> Judaism with all Jewish men, and<lb/> that it would
                be read by and would<lb/> benefit the American Port. Jews; who like<lb/> my self
                have known but little of the faith</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p>except its forms &amp;c—nothing of its<lb/> principle objects &amp; tendencies
                &amp;c.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I have lately seen a statement that<lb/> the K<add>?</add>ites of
                the <placeName>Crimea</placeName> are <add>?</add>, &amp;c.<lb/> The 1” edition of
                the Ks. in English that I have<lb/> seen <sic>a was is</sic> Travels in
                    <placeName>Russia</placeName> &amp;c by <persName>Dr. Clark</persName><lb/>
                about <date>1805</date>. We can put the book in <add>?</add>. But<lb/> only 5 or 6
                have since there was a settlement<lb/> of Ks. in the neighborhood of
                    <placeName>Bagdad</placeName>. Who<lb/> were Jews by descent undoubtedly and
                if<lb/> you wish it I can give you a refrence<add>?</add><lb/> to the authority—it
                is from Scotch Mission<lb/> any work in which I Saw it &amp; can again<lb/> send
                it.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">On the notes in your large <add>?</add> more<lb/> fall than is His
                    <add>?</add>
                <add>?</add>?</p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">Very respectfully</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">
                <hi rend="underline"><persName role="author">Saml. Judah</persName>.</hi>
            </p>
            <p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>Phila.</placeName>
            </p>
        </body>
